Generic single-database configuration with raw SQL migrations.

## Usage

### Create a new migration
```bash
cd src/backend
alembic revision -m "describe change"
# Edit alembic/versions/xxx_describe_change.py
```

### Run migrations
```bash
alembic upgrade head
```

### Rollback one migration
```bash
alembic downgrade -1
```

### View current version
```bash
alembic current
```

## In Kubernetes
Migrations run automatically in an initContainer before the backend starts.
See `k8s/base/deployment-backend.yaml`.
